.TH "hw_usb_set_address" 9 "hw_usb_set_address" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hw_usb_set_address \- configures USB address (execute without interruption)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" hw_usb_set_address
.BI "(struct ci_hdrc *ci "  ","
.BI "u8 value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ci" 12
the controller
.IP "value" 12
new USB address
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function explicitly sets the address, without the "USBADRA" (advance)
feature, which is not supported by older versions of the controller.
